{
  "texts": [
    "Models Genesis [41], [126] used image restoration as a pretext task, effectively capturing fine-grained visual information.",
    "c) CL-based pre-training in VFMs contrasts the similarities or differences between images to learn discriminative vision representations.",
    "These works [18], [130]- [135] learn discriminative visual features by ensuring that a query image is close to its positive samples and far from its negative samples in the embedding space.",
    "With the success of the CL in natural images, some works also utilized the MoCo [113] or Sim-CLR [136] algorithms on medical images, achieving success in pathology [130], [133] and X-ray [132] images.",
    "C2L [131] constructed homogeneous and heterogeneous data pairs and compared different image representations to learn general and robust features."
  ]
}